## üé® COLOR PALETTE STRATEGY

### Primary Palette (To Be Defined)

**Tier 1: Primary Brand Color (1-2 colors)**
- Main color for logo, headings, key elements
- Must have good contrast with white and black
- Should evoke technology + innovation

**Tier 2: Secondary Colors (2-3 colors)**
- Supporting colors for hierarchy
- One "Detroit Pride" color (warm)
- One "Growth/Energy" color (bright)
- Neutral supporting color (gray)

**Tier 3: Neutrals (1-2 colors)**
- Black/very dark gray (#111111 or similar)
- White/off-white (#FFFFFF or #F5F5F5)
- Medium gray for lighter backgrounds

### Accessibility Requirements

**WCAG AA Compliance:**
- ‚úÖ All color pairs minimum 4.5:1 contrast for text
- ‚úÖ 3:1 contrast minimum for graphics/UI elements
- ‚úÖ Not reliant on color alone for information (use patterns/texture too)
- ‚úÖ Test all combinations for colorblind accessibility

