## üî§ TYPOGRAPHY STRATEGY

### Heading Font
**Requirements:**
- Modern, sans-serif
- Strong personality (distinctive)
- Professional appearance
- Family with multiple weights (bold available)

**Candidates:**
- Open-source: Inter, Poppins, Raleway, Work Sans
- Google Fonts: Roboto, Montserrat, Ubuntu
- Premium: SF Pro Display, Futura, DIN

**Use:** All headings, logo text (if any), major callouts

### Body Font
**Requirements:**
- Highly readable (substantial x-height)
- Professional but warm
- Pairs well with heading font
- Strong numerals (for data/statistics)

**Candidates:**
- Open-source: Inter, IBM Plex Sans, Outfit
- Google Fonts: Lato, Open Sans, Source Sans Pro
- Premium: San Francisco, Helvetica Neue

**Use:** Body text, paragraphs, documentation

### Display/Logo Font
**Options:**
1. Use heading font (simpler, more cohesive)
2. Custom designed mark (more distinctive)
3. Licensed specialty font (premium feel)

**Recommendation:** Start with heading font, explore custom if budget allows

